Samsung announced it is looking into reports of issues with the touchscreen on its Galaxy S9 and S9+ smartphones, Engadget reported. Users have complained on Reddit and Samsung’s support forums about spots in the touchscreen display which have problems registering touches. The extent of these problems vary between users, with certain owners resolving the issue by increasing touch sensitivity in the device’s settings menu. Samsung said it was working on the problem and issued a statement regarding the reported issues. “We are looking into a limited number of reports of Galaxy S9/S9+ touchscreen responsiveness issues. We are working with affected customers and investigating,” said Samsung.